      <akn:section eId="sec_8_1772_02">
        <akn:num>8-1772.02</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Commercial property energy conservation.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_8-1772_02_1">
      <akn:num>(1)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>During a reasonable period of ingress and egress of people or the delivery or shipping of goods;</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_8-1772_02_2">
      <akn:num>(2)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Where the door is intended for vehicular access to or for a loading dock;</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_8-1772_02_3">
      <akn:num>(3)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>When an emergency situation exists requiring an exterior door or window to be kept open; or</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_8-1772_02_4">
      <akn:num>(4)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>When a commercial property implements an alternative strategy authorized by the Mayor through regulation as a reasonably equivalent means of conserving energy.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
